article.headline: Hampton 65, N. Carolina A&T 47
article.story: HAMPTON, Va. (AP) -- Devin Green scored 25 points and pulled down 13 rebounds, his sixth double-double of the season, to lead Hampton to victory over North Carolina A&T 65-47 Saturday. Bruce Brown added 15 points and nine rebounds to the Pirates' (11-11, 9-4 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) ninth consecutive win over the Aggies. Green and Brown combined for 24 points in the first half, putting the game all but out of reach. Cold shooting plagued the Aggies (4-19, 3-9) throughout the game, but especially in the first half where they shot just 6-of-25 from the field. Rechodd Carter scored nine points for the Aggies. ^
